---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Notice" description="How GyulRose Cakes uses personal information submitted through the website." noindex={true}>
  <section class="section"><div class="container prose"><p class="eyebrow">Draft for client confirmation</p><h1>Privacy notice</h1><p>This local prototype collects information only when someone submits a cake enquiry. Before deployment, the business owner must confirm the retention period, lawful basis, processors and deletion contact details.</p><h2>Information requested</h2><p>Name, phone number, email address, event details, postcode, cake preferences, allergy information and any reference link voluntarily supplied.</p><h2>Why it is used</h2><p>To assess availability, prepare and discuss a quote, fulfil an accepted order, communicate about collection or delivery and keep necessary business records.</p><h2>Who receives it</h2><p>GyulRose Cakes and the services used to deliver the enquiry workflow. The current workflow uses a website form and n8n automation. The final list of processors must be confirmed before publication.</p><h2>How long it is kept</h2><p>The owner must define and insert a proportionate retention period before deployment. Enquiry information should not be kept indefinitely without a business or legal reason.</p><h2>Your questions</h2><p>Contact <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> to ask about personal information connected to an enquiry.</p><p><strong>Status:</strong> this is a transparent implementation draft, not a substitute for owner review or professional legal advice.</p></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
